WEBVTT

00:00:01.080 --> 00:00:01.400
Alright!

00:00:01.880 --> 00:00:04.440
Let's add your first server. Two commands and

00:00:04.440 --> 00:00:04.920
you're set.

00:00:05.897 --> 00:00:08.697
There are two pieces. The command-line tool

00:00:08.697 --> 00:00:11.737
runs on your laptop, and an orchestrator

00:00:11.737 --> 00:00:14.457
called renet runs on the server. The

00:00:14.457 --> 00:00:17.417
CLI talks to it over SSH, so

00:00:17.417 --> 00:00:19.977
you never need to log into the server manually.

00:00:23.281 --> 00:00:25.976
Register the server from the command line.

00:00:25.976 --> 00:00:27.901
You give it a name,

00:00:27.901 --> 00:00:29.056
its IP address,

00:00:29.056 --> 00:00:30.596
and the SSH user.

00:00:30.596 --> 00:00:33.291
The name is just a local alias.

00:00:33.291 --> 00:00:35.986
We use machine-11 so it matches the

00:00:35.986 --> 00:00:36.370
IP,

00:00:36.370 --> 00:00:39.065
but it can be anything you like,

00:00:39.065 --> 00:00:40.990
such as prod-db or web-1.

00:00:40.990 --> 00:00:43.300
There is no separate init step;

00:00:43.300 --> 00:00:45.995
the config file is created automatically on

00:00:45.995 --> 00:00:46.765
first use.

00:00:48.765 --> 00:00:49.735
Server registered.

00:00:49.735 --> 00:00:52.161
Host keys were scanned automatically.

00:00:55.471 --> 00:00:57.390
Next we provision the server.

00:00:57.390 --> 00:01:00.077
This installs renet and creates the encrypted

00:01:00.077 --> 00:01:00.460
datastore.

00:01:05.359 --> 00:01:05.745
Done.

00:01:05.745 --> 00:01:08.447
Renet is installed and the datastore is

00:01:08.447 --> 00:01:08.833
ready.

00:01:15.087 --> 00:01:17.882
Here is the file that holds

00:01:17.882 --> 00:01:18.348
everything:

00:01:18.348 --> 00:01:19.280
your machines,

00:01:19.280 --> 00:01:20.677
the SSH key,

00:01:20.677 --> 00:01:22.075
and infrastructure settings.

00:01:22.075 --> 00:01:23.938
It is plain JSON,

00:01:23.938 --> 00:01:24.870
created automatically.

00:01:24.870 --> 00:01:27.199
You can keep several configs,

00:01:27.199 --> 00:01:29.994
one per environment such as production

00:01:29.994 --> 00:01:30.926
or staging,

00:01:30.926 --> 00:01:33.721
and switch between them with the

00:01:33.721 --> 00:01:34.653
config flag.

00:01:36.403 --> 00:01:37.409
One portable file.

00:01:37.409 --> 00:01:40.094
Copy it to another laptop to drive the

00:01:40.094 --> 00:01:40.765
same servers.

00:01:41.682 --> 00:01:44.242
And that's a wrap on adding a server! See you in

00:01:44.242 --> 00:01:44.882
the next one.
